<title>CANADA: IBM wins Alberta heath system contract.</title>
<headline>IBM wins Alberta heath system contract.</headline>
<dateline>EDMONTON 1997-07-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Alberta government said on Monday it selected International Business Machines Corp unit IBM Canada Ltd as an alliance partner to develop a blueprint for the Western Canadian province's new health information system.</p>
<p>Alberta said IBM would be working with a consortium of firms including TELUS Corp and three local information management and technology firms to develop the system, which could cost between C$200 million and C$300 million over the next five years.  </p>
<p>The three Alberta firms included CGI Information Systems and Management Consultants Inc, EDM Management Systems Inc and Sierra Systems Consultants Inc.</p>
<p>The government said the new system and related initiatives would use technology to link personal health information and ensure privacy under the name Alberta Wellnet.</p>
<p>The spending represents about 1.5 percent of Alberta's annual health care budget.</p>
<p>((Reuters Calgary Bureau (403) 531-1624))</p>
